article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 83, Henderson St. 81
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- LaQuentin Miles pulled down 12 rebounds and scored a game-high 29 points, including the go-ahead layup with 54 seconds left in overtime, to lift Central Arkansas over Henderson State 83-81 on Wednesday night. The Bears (5-3) were down 81-80 in extra play when Miles put in the layup. He was later fouled with 1 second left and missed the first free throw before making the second. Jarvis Garner helped out the Bears with 19 points and a game-high 14 rebounds. He sent the game into overtime with a 3-pointer at the buzzer in regulation. Andrew Ensley scored 16 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for the Reddies (3-4) while Denzel Lyles added 20 points and Deoirvay Johnson 15. The Reddies were more accurate from the field, shooting 45 percent compared to Central Arkansas' 38.
